---

### ðŸ§© **Option 1: Install using pip (Recommended)**

This is the most common and simplest way.

#### **Step 1: Update your system**

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
```

#### **Step 2: Install Python and pip (if not installed)**

```bash
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip -y
```

#### **Step 3: Install Jupyter Notebook**

```bash
pip install notebook
```

#### **Step 4: Run Jupyter Notebook**

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

ðŸ’¡ It will open automatically in your default web browser at:

```
http://localhost:8888
```

---

### ðŸ§± **Option 2: Install via Anaconda (Optional, for data science)**

If you use Anaconda, it comes with Jupyter preinstalled.

#### **Step 1: Download Anaconda**

```bash
wget https://repo.anaconda.com/archive/Anaconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
```

#### **Step 2: Run the installer**

```bash
bash Anaconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
```

Follow on-screen prompts, then restart your terminal.

#### **Step 3: Run Jupyter**

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

